<br>
This discussion was talked about the other night in a group.  I (warrior) put on a gimp shield I had in my inventory, and my fleshgrinder (killing hobs in PoN).  I was working on my bashing skills when the conversation came up about warriors never using shields.  At one point in EQ history, people said that warriors shouldnt use 2hs unless for their epic.  With new items out there, and the reposts from hell on PoP, 2hs is the way to go for most exp. groups.  (I use a Windblade in PoP, Fleshgrinder and Snowchipper for Old world and raids).<br>
<br>
My rambling point is, shields give some awesome stats to those who can carry them.  Resists, AC, HP, and the like.  With a crappy little charred gaurdian shield giving 25ac and 50hp, that item would be nice if it actually did some damage.<br>
<br>
No, I havent seen past teir 2.  No, I havent killed alot of boss mobs.  So if their are shields out there for warriors that I dont know about, dont flame me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But I have yet to see a main warrior in a grp or raid use a shield.  <br>
